  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your tandoor to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Grease the tandoor with a little butter and place almond slices in the bottom.",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine almond flour, muscovado sugar, eggs, melted butter, almond extract, vanilla extract, all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt. Mix until smooth and well combined.",
    "Pour the batter evenly into the greased tandoor.",
    "Cook in the tandoor for about 20-30 minutes or until golden brown on top and crispy.",
    "Let it cool slightly before slicing and serving."
